#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:7 b1223f69342549009e436b71bbca5ec7
msgid "Multi-factor authentication within particular qubes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:10 c39a4e99f1914f75a2f5862ca2223968
msgid ""
"Most use cases for the hardware tokens can be achieved exactly as "
"described by the manufacturer or other instructions found online. One "
"usually just needs to attach the token (e.g. YubiKey) to the "
"corresponding app qube to get the same result (see the documentation on "
"how to use :doc:`USB devices </user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-usb-"
"devices>` in Qubes OS accordingly). The recommended way for using CTAP in"
" Qubes is described :doc:`here </user/security-in-qubes/ctap-proxy>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:13 7884e85bf3944bf7a2e4feceed7b5e43
msgid "Multi-factor login for Qubes OS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:16 42657f78d081408eacace80bd413cfe0
msgid ""
"By default Qubes has two protection mechanisms against attackers. The "
"first is full disk encryption and the second the user login screen / "
"lockscreen. This article section concerns only adding multi-factor "
"authentication to the second one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:19 caa89f2c5da24824b7e1d9881bccc04e
msgid "Time-based One-time Password (TOTP)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:22 83163526a4ae479ab51ff633a7da5537
msgid ""
"As the name implies, this generates authentication code that is time-"
"dependent. You can save the TOTP secret in a mobile app like `FreeOTP "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FreeOTP>`__ and then use it as an "
"additional factor to login to your Qubes system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:24 44598f9d38454068a81ef8678b0511f5
msgid "**Warning**: remember to keep backup access codes."
msgstr ""

