msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:225 168a26a2c76244cdb367b6e8e9c5a616
msgid "use ``fixed 64 bit input`` for ``HMAC-SHA1 mode``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:227 1e76e765120542d6841ae161cc06f15c
msgid ""
"insert the YubiKey (if not done already) and make sure that it is "
"attached to the vm,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:229 368a5e1b7a584a64b83af2e4377f9b1b
msgid "press ``Write Configuration`` once you are ready."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:237 967ae63e4ee04256afe328fec8e523cd
msgid ""
"Set up a new NK3 Secrets App HOTP secret by attaching the NitroKey to "
"your USB qube and running the following commands in it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:246 3026d279bdc4488495a0c5c09d0bd3b7
msgid ""
"Note that the 20 digit sequence can contain any printable ASCII "
"character, e.g. letters, numbers, punctuation marks. The actual ``Secret "
"Key (base 32)`` is the base32 encoded form of that sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:252 d39dd55afafb4a47b0d6498296039531
msgid ""
"We will call the ``Secret Key (20 bytes hex)`` (YubiKey) or ``Secret Key "
"(base 32)`` ``AESKEY``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:254 86704e4b2efb48dd915f0940e7c3a2e8
msgid ""
"It is recommended to keep a backup of your ``AESKEY`` in an offline VM "
"used as a vault."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:256 895a3feeb0224ce986fb44c77f2e190d
msgid ""
"Consider keeping a backup of your ``AESKEY`` on paper and storing it in a"
" safe place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:258 c3113f956e4546a4bd47445ccbe6c5cb
msgid ""
"If you have multiple YubiKeys for backup purposes (in case one gets lost,"
" stolen or breaks) you can write the same settings into other YubiKeys. "
"For YubiKeys you can choose “Program multiple YubiKeys” in the program; "
"make sure to select ``Same secret for all keys`` in this case. For "
"NitroKeys you can set up the secret for multiple of them, but you must "
"always use the same NitroKey, because the HOTP counter will be "
"incremented in dom0 as well as the used NitroKey whenever you make use of"
" this method. If you want to switch to a different NitroKey later, delete"
" the file ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/nk-hotp-counter`` in dom0 first to make it"
" work with a fresh NitroKey 3. Do the same if for some reason your "
"counters get desynchronized (it stops working), e.g. due to connectivity "
"issues (NitroKey3A Minis are known to wear out quickly)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:268 82636bd15de34a0a8e747828c8c139f3
msgid ""
"Paste your ``AESKEY`` into ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/yk-secret-key.hex`` in "
"dom0. Note that if you had previously used a NitroKey3 with this package,"
" you *must* delete the file ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/nk-hotp-secret`` or its "
"content!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:272 f7e835919d1e494bb48040ff4821627b
msgid ""
"Create the file ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/nk-hotp-secret`` in dom0 and paste "
"your ``AESKEY`` (in base 32 format) into it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:278 5a762f22608a4dccb0eb294611cf13c5
msgid ""
"As mentioned before, you need to define a new password that is only used "
"in combination with the YubiKey / NitroKey3. You can write this password "
"in plain text into ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/login-pass`` in dom0. This is "
"considered safe as dom0 is ultimately trusted anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:280 2bcb6bcca59b437ca0333986cc83ef22
msgid ""
"However, if you prefer you can paste a hashed password instead into "
"``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/login-pass-hashed.hex`` in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:282 7ca36c9c13ba411fba8741298bbfb4bd
msgid ""
"You can calculate your hashed password using the following two commands. "
"First run the following command to store your password in a temporary "
"variable ``password``. (This way your password will not leak to the "
"terminal command history file.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:290 a886fe186a3544639a4b9ae83c60bdf6
msgid "Now run the following command to calculate your hashed password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:300 f77de8b77ed14e01924f0af3b9cee1b3
msgid "To enable multi-factor authentication for a service, you need to add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:307 57650d77f3cf47c295e1c1916179ae48
msgid ""
"(same for YubiKey and NitroKey3) to the corresponding service file in "
"``/etc/pam.d/`` in dom0. This means, if you want to enable the login via "
"YubiKey / NitroKey3 for xscreensaver (the default screen lock program), "
"you add the line at the beginning of ``/etc/pam.d/xscreensaver``. If you "
"want to use the login for a tty shell, add it to ``/etc/pam.d/login``. "
"Add it to ``/etc/pam.d/lightdm`` if you want to enable the login for the "
"default display manager and so on. It is important, that ``auth include "
"yubikey`` is added at the beginning of these files, otherwise it will "
"most likely not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/mfa.rst:310 5f9c01a7d996421eb91ff8936f02cb46
msgid ""
"Adjust the USB VM name in case you are using something other than the "
"default ``sys-usb`` by editing ``/etc/qubes/yk-keys/vm`` in dom0."
msgstr ""

